<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="138" pageId="3" pageNumber="133" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[491,1532,348,578]" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">
Diagnosis — Body size: 281 × 135–143. Rostral, lamellar and interlamellar setae short, narrowly phylliform, smooth. Bothridial setae of medium size, spathulate. Notogaster with hump-like median part and anterolateral and posterolateral concavities. Notogastral setae short, narrowly phylliform, smooth, setae 
<emphasis box="[878,905,450,474]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">da</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[920,952,450,474]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">dm</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[967,994,450,474]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">dp</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[1009,1036,450,474]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">lm</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[1050,1071,450,474]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">lp</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[1086,1099,450,474]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">h</emphasis>
<subScript attach="left" box="[1099,1108,462,479]" fontSize="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">1</subScript>
, 
<emphasis box="[1125,1138,450,474]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">h</emphasis>
<subScript attach="left" box="[1138,1147,462,479]" fontSize="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">2</subScript>
inserted in a longitudinal row dorsomedially. Subcapitular setae 
<emphasis box="[857,870,484,508]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">h</emphasis>
shorter than 
<emphasis box="[1009,1022,485,508]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">a</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1074,1093,485,508]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">m</emphasis>
. Epimeral, genital, aggenital and anal setae short, setiform, smooth. Adanal setae slightly phylliform, smooth. Leg tarsi IV with 11 setae (
<emphasis box="[560,600,553,576]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">pv”</emphasis>
absent), setae 
<emphasis box="[756,778,553,577]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">l”</emphasis>
of genua I, II dilated distally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[491,1547,655,1910]" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">
Description — Measurements – Medium size. Body length: 281 (
<typeStatus box="[1242,1340,655,679]" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">holotype</typeStatus>
, male), 281 (one 
<typeStatus box="[491,581,690,714]" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">paratype</typeStatus>
, male); notogaster width: 143 (
<typeStatus box="[936,1036,689,713]" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">holotype</typeStatus>
), 135 (
<typeStatus box="[1109,1203,689,713]" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">paratype</typeStatus>
). Integument (
<figureCitation box="[1365,1458,689,713]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[119,186,1950,1971]" captionTargetBox="[137,1460,261,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-2@4.[115,1483,231,1896]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1 Hardybodes minutus n. sp.: A – dorsal view; B – ventral view (legs except trochanters III, IV not illustrated). Scale bar 45 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4487473" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4487473/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">Figs 1A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1470,1504,689,713]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[119,186,1938,1959]" captionTargetBox="[95,1502,252,2008]" captionTargetId="figure-2@5.[6,1562,198,1982]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2 Hardybodes minutus n. sp.: A – anterior part of body, lateral view (legs except trochanter III not illustrated); B – posterior part of body, lateral view (legs except trochanter IV not illustrated). Scale bar 45 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4487477" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4487477/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">2B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[491,524,724,748]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="7.[119,186,1938,1959]" captionTargetBox="[204,1388,230,1855]" captionTargetId="figure-2@7.[196,1401,222,1885]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 4 Hardybodes minutus n. sp.: A – trochanter, femur and genu of leg I, right, antiaxial view; B – leg II (trochanter partially covered by pedotectum II), right, antiaxial view; C – leg III except tarsus, left, antiaxial view; D – leg IV, left, antiaxial view. Scale bar 15 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4487481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4487481/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">4B</figureCitation>
) – Body brown. Body (including genital and anal plates, subcapitular mentum and genae) and legs densely granulate (diameter of granules up to 1), notogaster and some leg segments partially tuberculate (diameter of tubercles up to 8).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[491,1547,655,1910]" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">
Prodorsum (
<figureCitation box="[668,737,826,850]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[119,186,1950,1971]" captionTargetBox="[137,1460,261,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-2@4.[115,1483,231,1896]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1 Hardybodes minutus n. sp.: A – dorsal view; B – ventral view (legs except trochanters III, IV not illustrated). Scale bar 45 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4487473" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4487473/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">Figs 1</figureCitation>
A–B, 2A, 3A) — Rostrum broadly rounded. Lamellae slightly shorter than prodorsum, broadly triangular distally. Rostral (10), lamellar (10) and interlamellar (10– 12) setae narrowly phylliform, smooth. Bothridial setae (36–41) with short stalk and longer, spathulate, barbed head. Exobothridial setae and their alveoli absent. Tutoria with triangular tip. Anterolateral parts of prodorsum with pair of concavities.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[491,1547,655,1910]" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">
Notogaster (
<figureCitation box="[670,740,997,1021]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[119,186,1950,1971]" captionTargetBox="[137,1460,261,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-2@4.[115,1483,231,1896]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1 Hardybodes minutus n. sp.: A – dorsal view; B – ventral view (legs except trochanters III, IV not illustrated). Scale bar 45 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4487473" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4487473/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">Figs 1</figureCitation>
A–B, 2A–B, 3B) — Median part elongate, hump-like. Anterolateral and posterolateral parts with one large concavity. Humeral shoulders indistinct in dorsal view. Fifteen pairs of notogastral setae short (4–6), narrowly phylliform, smooth; of these, seven pairs (
<emphasis box="[559,586,1099,1123]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">da</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[599,631,1099,1123]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">dm</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[646,673,1099,1123]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">dp</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[686,713,1099,1123]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">lm</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[726,747,1099,1123]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">lp</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[761,774,1099,1123]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">h</emphasis>
<subScript attach="left" box="[774,783,1111,1128]" fontSize="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">1</subScript>
, 
<emphasis box="[799,812,1099,1123]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">h</emphasis>
<subScript attach="left" box="[812,821,1111,1128]" fontSize="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">2</subScript>
) inserted in longitudinal row dorsomedially, 
<emphasis box="[1305,1317,1100,1123]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">c</emphasis>
<subScript attach="left" box="[1317,1326,1111,1128]" fontSize="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">1</subScript>
and 
<emphasis box="[1380,1407,1099,1123]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">da</emphasis>
located close to each other. Lyrifissures, opisthonotal gland openings and circumgastric sigilla band well visible.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[491,1547,655,1910]" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">
Gnathosoma (
<figureCitation box="[685,754,1202,1226]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="6.[119,186,1938,1959]" captionTargetBox="[145,1443,256,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-2@6.[129,1468,219,1885]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 3 Hardybodes minutus n. sp.: A – prodorsum, frontal view; B – posterior view; C – subcapitulum, ventral view; D – palp, right, antiaxial view; E – chelicera, left, paraxial view. Scale bar 45 μm (A, B), scale bar 15 μm (C–E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4487479" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4487479/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">Figs 3</figureCitation>
C–E) — Subcapitulum longer than wide (57–61 × 49–53). Subcapitular setae (
<emphasis box="[560,573,1237,1260]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">a</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[586,605,1237,1260]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">m</emphasis>
, 6–8; 
<emphasis box="[672,685,1236,1260]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">h</emphasis>
, 4–6) setiform, smooth. Adoral setae and their alveoli absent. Palps (32–36) with setation 0–2–1–3–8(+ω), 
<emphasis box="[818,862,1271,1294]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">acm</emphasis>
absent. Solenidia (1/2 length of palptarsi) thickened, bluntended, pressed to the palptarsal surface. Postpalpal setae (2) spiniform, smooth. Chelicerae (57–65) with two setiform, barbed setae, 
<emphasis box="[939,977,1338,1362]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">cha</emphasis>
(16–18) longer than 
<emphasis box="[1208,1246,1338,1362]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">chb</emphasis>
(10–12). Trägårdh’s organ tapered.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[491,1547,655,1910]" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">
Epimeral and lateral podosomal regions (
<figureCitation box="[987,1078,1407,1431]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[119,186,1950,1971]" captionTargetBox="[137,1460,261,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-2@4.[115,1483,231,1896]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1 Hardybodes minutus n. sp.: A – dorsal view; B – ventral view (legs except trochanters III, IV not illustrated). Scale bar 45 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4487473" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4487473/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">Figs 1B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1090,1123,1407,1431]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[119,186,1938,1959]" captionTargetBox="[95,1502,252,2008]" captionTargetId="figure-2@5.[6,1562,198,1982]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2 Hardybodes minutus n. sp.: A – anterior part of body, lateral view (legs except trochanter III not illustrated); B – posterior part of body, lateral view (legs except trochanter IV not illustrated). Scale bar 45 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4487477" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4487477/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">2A</figureCitation>
) — Epimeral setal formula 3–1–3–3. All setae short (4), setiform, smooth. Pedotecta I represented by large and broad scales, pedotecta II are small scales, broadly triangular, rounded distally in ventral view. Discidia triangular, rounded distally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[491,1547,655,1910]" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">
Anogenital region (
<figureCitation box="[751,843,1543,1567]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[119,186,1950,1971]" captionTargetBox="[137,1460,261,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-2@4.[115,1483,231,1896]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1 Hardybodes minutus n. sp.: A – dorsal view; B – ventral view (legs except trochanters III, IV not illustrated). Scale bar 45 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4487473" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4487473/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">Figs 1B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[855,889,1543,1567]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[119,186,1938,1959]" captionTargetBox="[95,1502,252,2008]" captionTargetId="figure-2@5.[6,1562,198,1982]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2 Hardybodes minutus n. sp.: A – anterior part of body, lateral view (legs except trochanter III not illustrated); B – posterior part of body, lateral view (legs except trochanter IV not illustrated). Scale bar 45 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4487477" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4487477/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">2B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[900,932,1543,1567]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="6.[119,186,1938,1959]" captionTargetBox="[145,1443,256,1793]" captionTargetId="figure-2@6.[129,1468,219,1885]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 3 Hardybodes minutus n. sp.: A – prodorsum, frontal view; B – posterior view; C – subcapitulum, ventral view; D – palp, right, antiaxial view; E – chelicera, left, paraxial view. Scale bar 45 μm (A, B), scale bar 15 μm (C–E)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4487479" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4487479/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">3B</figureCitation>
) — With indistinct concavities and ridges. Four pairs of genital, one pair of aggenital and two pairs of anal setae short (4–6) setiform, smooth. Three pairs of adanal setae (
<emphasis box="[726,753,1612,1636]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">ad</emphasis>
<subScript attach="left" box="[754,763,1624,1641]" fontSize="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">1</subScript>
, 
<emphasis box="[779,806,1612,1636]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">ad</emphasis>
<subScript attach="left" box="[806,815,1624,1641]" fontSize="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">2</subScript>
, 6–8; 
<emphasis box="[886,913,1612,1636]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">ad</emphasis>
<subScript attach="left" box="[914,923,1624,1641]" fontSize="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">3</subScript>
, 4–6) slightly phylliform, smooth, 
<emphasis box="[1302,1329,1612,1636]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">ad</emphasis>
<subScript attach="left" box="[1330,1339,1624,1641]" fontSize="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">1</subScript>
, 
<emphasis box="[1355,1382,1612,1636]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">ad</emphasis>
<subScript attach="left" box="[1382,1391,1624,1641]" fontSize="7" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">2</subScript>
inserted on the arch-like ridge posterior to the anal aperture. Adanal lyrifissures not discerned under the cerotegumental layer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[491,1547,655,1910]" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">
Legs (
<figureCitation box="[606,681,1714,1738]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="7.[119,186,1938,1959]" captionTargetBox="[204,1388,230,1855]" captionTargetId="figure-2@7.[196,1401,222,1885]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 4 Hardybodes minutus n. sp.: A – trochanter, femur and genu of leg I, right, antiaxial view; B – leg II (trochanter partially covered by pedotectum II), right, antiaxial view; C – leg III except tarsus, left, antiaxial view; D – leg IV, left, antiaxial view. Scale bar 15 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4487481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4487481/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="133">Figs 4</figureCitation>
